HB 221 Reengrossed 2026 Regular Session Echols
Designates the new Mississippi River bridge connecting La. Hwy. 1 to La. Hwy. 30 as the
"President Donald J. Trump Expressway".
Specifies that proposed law will become effective if and when the federal government
provides a substantial amount of funding for construction of the bridge, but only if such
funding is provided prior to noon on Jan. 20, 2029.
Directs the Dept. of Transportation and Development (DOTD) to erect and maintain
appropriate signage reflecting this designation once the bridge is constructed, provided local
or private monies are received by the DOTD equal to its actual cost for material, fabrication,
mounting posts, and installation of the signage, not to exceed the sum of $750 per sign.
Summary of Amendments Adopted by House
The House Floor Amendments to the engrossed bill:
1. Make technical changes
2. Provide that the effectiveness of proposed law is contingent upon funding from
the federal government for the construction of the bridge by Noon on January 20,
2029.
